AB  - One of the first tenets of international business (IB) is that it spans multiple disciplines. Yet driven by the need to publish in specialist journals or by the disciplinary expertise of individual authors, most studies at best pay lip service to this aspect of the field. It is perfectly possible to do deep and meaningful IB research through a single disciplinary lens. However, using the analytical tools of multiple disciplines can make for richer analysis (Agrawal & Hoetker, 2007). Frederick Guy's ambitious book is an attempt at such an inquiry.
